This article discusses the debate surrounding the repeal of President Obama's health care reform, also known as the Affordable Care Act. Some editorials argue that repealing the law would be a mistake, as it reduces the deficit and provides important benefits such as coverage for pre-existing conditions and extended coverage for children. Others criticize the Republican push for repeal, calling it hypocritical given their claims to reduce the deficit and improve the economy. Overall, the article highlights the division and controversy surrounding the issue of health care reform.